## CLI Reference

```bash
$ causal-qd --help
```

<!-- verified output -->
```
Usage: causal-qd [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...

  CausalQD — Quality-Diversity for Causal Discovery.

  A framework for illuminating the space of causal models using MAP-Elites
  with certificate-guided quality metrics.

Options:
  --verbose / --quiet  Enable verbose logging.
  --version            Show the version and exit.
  --help               Show this message and exit.

Commands:
  benchmark    Run standard benchmark experiments.
  certificate  Compute robustness certificates for the best DAG in results.
  evaluate     Evaluate experiment results against a ground-truth DAG.
  from-pandas  Show how to export a pandas DataFrame for use with causal-qd.
  run          Run a CausalQD MAP-Elites experiment.
  visualize    Generate visualisation plots from experiment results.
```

### `causal-qd run`

Run a MAP-Elites experiment on observational data.

```
Options:
  --config PATH                   Path to YAML/JSON config file.
  --data PATH                     Observational data (CSV, NPZ, Parquet).  [required]
  --n-vars INTEGER                Number of variables (auto-detected if omitted).
  --n-generations INTEGER         Number of MAP-Elites generations.
  --batch-size INTEGER            Offspring per generation.
  --archive-type [grid|cvt]       Archive type.
  --score-type [bic|bdeu|bge]     Scoring function type.
  --output PATH                   Output directory.  [default: results]
  --seed INTEGER                  Random seed.  [default: 42]
  --n-workers INTEGER             Number of parallel workers.  [default: 1]
  --n-bootstrap INTEGER           Bootstrap samples for certificates.
  --output-format [text|json|csv] Output format.  [default: text]
  --ground-truth PATH             Ground-truth DAG for automatic evaluation.
```

### `causal-qd evaluate`

Evaluate saved results against a ground-truth DAG.  Computes QD-score,
coverage, SHD, F1, precision, and recall.

```
Options:
  --results PATH            Results directory.  [required]
  --true-dag PATH           Ground-truth DAG (CSV or DOT).
  --format [text|json|csv]  Output format.  [default: text]
```

### `causal-qd visualize`

Generate convergence, coverage, QD-score, and multi-panel summary plots.

```
Options:
  --results PATH          Results directory.  [required]
  --output PATH           Plot output directory.
  --format [png|pdf|svg]  Image format.  [default: png]
  --dpi INTEGER           Resolution.  [default: 150]
```

### `causal-qd benchmark`

Run synthetic benchmark experiments with optional baseline comparisons.

```
Options:
  --n-nodes INTEGER               Number of nodes.  [default: 5]
  --n-samples INTEGER             Data samples.  [default: 1000]
  --n-generations INTEGER         Generations.  [default: 200]
  --batch-size INTEGER            Batch size.  [default: 20]
  --seed INTEGER                  Random seed.  [default: 42]
  --output PATH                   Output directory.  [default: benchmark_results]
  --include-baselines / --no-baselines
                                  Run baseline algorithms for comparison.
```

### `causal-qd certificate`

Compute bootstrap robustness certificates for edges in the best DAG.

```
Options:
  --results PATH         Results directory.  [required]
  --data PATH            Observational data.  [required]
  --n-bootstrap INTEGER  Bootstrap samples.  [default: 100]
  --n-workers INTEGER    Parallel workers.  [default: 1]
  --output PATH          Output file for certificates.
```

### `causal-qd from-pandas`

Display code snippets for exporting pandas DataFrames.

```
Options:
  --output PATH               Save snippet to file.
  --format [csv|parquet|npz]  Export format.  [default: csv]
```

