## Type System

All type aliases live in `causal_qd/types.py`:

| Type | Underlying | Description |
|------|-----------|-------------|
| `AdjacencyMatrix` | `NDArray[int8]` | n×n binary edge matrix |
| `DataMatrix` | `NDArray[float64]` | N×p observation matrix |
| `BehavioralDescriptor` | `NDArray[float64]` | d-dim descriptor vector |
| `QualityScore` | `float` | Scalar fitness (higher = better) |
| `CellIndex` | `Tuple[int, ...]` | Multi-dim archive cell index |
| `TopologicalOrder` | `List[int]` | Valid topological node ordering |
| `EdgeList` | `List[Tuple[int, int]]` | Directed edges as (src, tgt) |
| `GraphHash` | `int` | Canonical graph hash (e.g. nauty) |

Enums: `EdgeType` (directed/undirected/bidirected/none), `GraphType`
(dag/cpdag/pdag/mag/pag), `MutationType` (add/remove/reverse/composite),
`ScoreType` (bic/bdeu/bge/aic/log_likelihood).

Dataclasses: `Edge`, `MutationRecord`, `CrossoverRecord`,
`GraphProperties`, `ArchiveEntry`, `MutationConfig`.

